text: Kesgrave is a town on the eastern side of Ipswich in Suffolk. Its population is roughly around 14,000 people. To the west of Kesgrave, there is a town called Martlesham. Kesgrave has a historical church called Oscar Parkins' All Saints. == References == Category:Towns in Suffolk Category:Civil parishes in Suffolk Category:Ipswich Category:Suffolk Coastal
